The `linuxkit/firmware` package stored firmware in `/lib/firmware/<driver>/<fw-image>/<fw-image>` when it should have stored it in `/lib/firmware/<driver>/<fw-image>`.

This fixes https://github.com/linuxkit/linuxkit/issues/3392

While at it, also use a newer kernel to figure out which modules to install and update to the latest firmware images.

